      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "LINE AND SINKER (7) is progressing well scoring last time out (16.98) at this track and bringing up her 5th career win. Has never missed the frame here at the trip from eight starts. Ran one of the fastest times on the program in her latest win. Hard to go past. MARTINIQUE (8) is a capable type and proved too classy last time to win by 3.5 lengths at this track in a handy 17.24 beating Aussie Storm. Makes plenty of appeal if runs up to latest. LOCO PIRATA (1) has been beaten for early speed lately, last time finishing seventh (17.96) in a Grade 5 at this track. Form here sound including five wins. Reliable out of the boxes and should take advantage of the inside draw. Key player if finds best. WHERE'S RYDER (2) is worth another chance despite missing the top-three here most recently.",
